---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service — Pear Notes" description="Pear Notes Terms of Service. Read the terms and conditions for using the Pear Notes application.">
  <div class="dot-grid"></div>
  <Header />

  <section class="legal container">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: June 28, 2026</p>

    <p>
      These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of the Pear Notes application
      ("the app", "Pear Notes") on all platforms (iOS, Android, macOS, Windows).
      By downloading, installing, or using Pear Notes, you agree to be bound by these Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
    <p>
      By accessing or using Pear Notes, you acknowledge that you have read, understood,
      and agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree with any part of these
      Terms, you must not use the app.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
    <p>
      Pear Notes is a private, encrypted note-taking application that stores all data
      locally on your device. The app provides:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Encrypted note creation and editing</li>
      <li>Voice note recording and embedding</li>
      <li>Document scanning</li>
      <li>Peer-to-peer device synchronization</li>
      <li>AES-256 encrypted backup and restore</li>
      <li>Customizable typography and themes</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. User Responsibilities</h2>

    <h3>3.1 Data Ownership</h3>
    <p>
      You own all content you create within Pear Notes. Since all data is stored locally
      on your device and synced peer-to-peer, you are solely responsible for:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Maintaining backups of your data</li>
      <li>Safeguarding your 64-character private encryption key</li>
      <li>Managing the security of your devices</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3.2 Private Key Responsibility</h3>
    <p>
      Pear Notes generates a unique 64-character private key for encrypting your data
      and backups. <strong>This key cannot be recovered if lost.</strong> You are solely
      responsible for storing your private key securely. We cannot access, reset, or
      recover your encryption key or any data encrypted with it.
    </p>

    <h3>3.3 Acceptable Use</h3>
    <p>
      You agree to use Pear Notes in compliance with all applicable local, national,
      and international laws and regulations. You may not use the app to store or
      transmit content that violates any law.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Intellectual Property</h2>
    <p>
      The Pear Notes application, including its design, code, icons, and branding,
      is the intellectual property of Pear Notes and its developer. You are granted
      a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use the app for personal
      purposes in accordance with these Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Disclaimers</h2>

    <h3>5.1 No Warranty</h3>
    <p>
      Pear Notes is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind,
      either express or implied. We do not guarantee that the app will be error-free,
      uninterrupted, or free of harmful components.
    </p>

    <h3>5.2 Data Loss</h3>
    <p>
      Since all data is stored locally on your device, we are not responsible for data
      loss resulting from:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Device failure, damage, or theft</li>
      <li>Accidental deletion of notes or app data</li>
      <li>Loss of your private encryption key</li>
      <li>Operating system updates or app reinstallation</li>
      <li>Failure to maintain regular backups</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5.3 Peer-to-Peer Sync</h3>
    <p>
      While we strive to ensure reliable peer-to-peer synchronization, network conditions,
      NAT configurations, and device compatibility may affect sync performance. We do not
      guarantee that synchronization will always succeed in all network environments.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Pear Notes and its developer
      shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or
      punitive damages, including but not limited to loss of data, loss of profits,
      or business interruption, arising from your use of or inability to use the app.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Third-Party Content</h2>
    <p>
      Pear Notes may include links to third-party resources for convenience. We do not
      endorse, control, or assume responsibility for any third-party content or services.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Modifications to the Service</h2>
    <p>
      We reserve the right to modify, suspend, or discontinue any aspect of Pear Notes
      at any time without notice. We are not liable for any modification, suspension,
      or discontinuation of the app.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to Terms</h2>
    <p>
      We may revise these Terms from time to time. Updated Terms will be posted on
      this page with a revised "Last updated" date. Your continued use of Pear Notes
      after any changes constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Governing Law</h2>
    <p>
      These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of
      the jurisdiction in which the developer resides, without regard to conflict
      of law principles.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      If you have any questions about these Terms of Service, please contact us at:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:amreshcse007@gmail.com">amreshcse007@gmail.com</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
